article.headline: Arizona State 76, Oregon State 59
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- It's a modest two-game winning streak, but Arizona State will take it. Jeff Pendergraph scored 18 points and grabbed 11 rebounds -- his second double-double this season -- to lead the Sun Devils past Oregon State 76-59 Thursday night, dealing the Beavers their fifth straight loss and seventh in the last eight games. "We started a little streak. That's what we wanted to do," said Arizona State's Krevin Kruger, who scored 17 points. "But I think mainly we are having fun out there and we are playing with confidence. We are not getting down on ourselves. We're not letting one bad thing ruin the game." Bryson Krueger added 14 points, five rebounds and four assists in the first Sun Devil back-to-back wins since Dec. 21-22. It was just the third victory overall for Arizona State (9-12, 3-9 Pac-10) in 12 games and the first conference win at home. Sasa Cuic scored 23 points and grabbed five rebounds for the Beavers. Nick DeWitz added 16 points, all but three in the first half, for Oregon State (10-13, 3-9). "We're battling but offensively we have just been struggling for the past month," Beavers coach Jay John said. "There hasn't been a team in the Pac-10 to this point, after 12 games, that has shot 50 percent from the field against us for the game." Arizona State made 26 of 59 shots from the field but was 9 of 17 from behind the 3-point arc against the second-best defense in the conference against the shot. DeWitz, who leads the league with two blocks per game, knocked away four shots but was 0-for-3 from the field in the second half and 5-for-12 on the night, mostly against Pendergraph. Pendergraph made a short hook and Kruger hit consecutive 3-pointers to give Arizona State a 57-40 lead with 12:13 remaining. The Beavers never got closer than 14. "I know that maybe some people coming in didn't know a lot about Jeff Pendergraph," Sun Devils coach Rob Evans said. "But I think most everybody knows about him. He may not have been as heralded as some of the guys coming out in this league. I'm hard pressed to find anybody, a freshman, who is playing better than him right now." The Sun Devils committed a season-low eight turnovers. Kruger, who has been off any solid food for several days because of his ailing wisdom teeth, made 5 of 8 3-pointers as the Sun Devils hit a season-high nine 3-pointers. Arizona State went on an 11-4 run to end the first half for a 38-29 lead.
